messages.subject: Only One Week until the HENA 2009 Conference!
messages.msgSnippet: THE HENA CONFERENCE IS ONE WEEK FROM TODAY!!!!! We look forward to seeing you at the HENA 2009 conference on March 7, 2009 at ASU Memorial Union in Tempe!
messages.messageBody:
THE HENA CONFERENCE IS ONE WEEK FROM TODAY!!!!!

We look forward to seeing you at the HENA 2009 conference on
March 7, 2009 at ASU Memorial Union in Tempe!

Tomorrow, March 1, 2009 (yes, it's March already!) is the last
day to register online and have your registration badges waiting
for your speedy check in!  If you know you'll show, please do
register ahead of time to save time at check in and have a nice
printed badge instead of a handwritten one!  Register now at
[http://www.hena.us/conferenceRegistration.html%5d!

Our speaker schedule is now FULL, so check it out and plan your
day at http://www.hena.us/conferenceSchedule.html
[http://www.hena.us/ConferenceSchedule.html%5d and read about our
speakers at [http://www.hena.us/conferenceSpeaker.html%5d!

As always, the whole family are welcome!  Kids have low prices
and grandparents are free!

If you are homeschooling or just curious about homeschooling
DON'T MISS THIS EVENT! We are open to all and support families
that homeschool and children are welcome! Please feel free to
forward this notice!

We look forward to seeing you at the HENA 2009 conference on
March 7, 2009 at ASU Memorial Union in Tempe!

Register now at:  [http://hena.us/conferenceRegistration.html%5d

If you like the conference and want to see it continue, please do
contact us about volunteering.  The conference and HENA are all
volunteer run.  Email [hena@...] about volunteering for
next year!

Cindy Fox
HENA 2009 Conference Coordinator
[http://www.hena.us/conference.html%5d
602-692-8923

The Home Education Network of Arizona is an inclusive statewide
support organization that respects, values, and finds strength
in diversity. We are neutral in matters of religion and partisan
politics and we respect each other's educational choices. HENA's
mission is to create an environment in which all home educating
families in Arizona can share resources, find support, and build
community.

This email was sent to unschoolingbasics@yahoogroups.com. You can instantly unsubscribe
from these emails by clicking here http://homeeducationnetworkofarizona.cmail2.com/t/y/u/dkjjtu/stjdiijt/.
